cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning discriminative correlation filters, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) subcategories.
